# Auth Refresh

This endpoint is used to refresh the access token using the refresh token.

## Request

- Method: GET
- URL: {{BASE_URL}}/auth/refresh
- Headers:
    - Content-Type: application/json
- Body:
    - refreshToken (string, required): The refresh token used to obtain a new access token.

## Response

The response for this request is a JSON object with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "status": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "accessToken": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "refreshToken": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

- Status: 200 OK
- Content-Type: application/json
- Body:

    ``` json
    {
      "status": "",
      "data": {
        "accessToken": "",
        "refreshToken": ""
      }
    }

     ```

This endpoint is used to send a request to verify an email address. It expects a JSON payload with the email address in the request body.

### Request Body

- email (string, required): The email address to be verified.


### Response

The response will be in JSON format with the following schema:

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "status": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "data": {
            "type": "string"
        }
    }
}

 ```

The response will include the status and data properties, both of which are of type string.

### Password Reset Confirmation

